<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFFBFFE5E1FD0649FE48F9EE" bold="true" box="[199,491,1554,1581]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFFBFFE5E1FD0649FEE1F9EE" bold="true" box="[199,322,1554,1581]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">M. phoebe</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFFBFFE5E0BB0648FE48F9EE" bold="true" box="[385,491,1554,1581]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">uralensis</emphasis>
</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFFBFFE5E0CE0649FD65F9EE" author="Krulikovsky, A." box="[500,710,1555,1581]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" pagination="315 - 328" refId="ref9945" refString="Krulikovsky, A. (1897) Notes on the fauna Macrolepidoptera of the area of the city of Ufa. Metrialy k Pooznaniyu Fauny i Flory Rossiiskoi Imperialis, Otdel Zoologicheskij, 3, 315 - 328. [In Russian]" type="journal article" year="1897">Krulikovsky, 1897</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1BD8652DFFFBFFE5E3F50649FDF8F81E" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="537D36A6FFFBFFE5E3F50649FDF8F81E" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,2013]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">
[TL: District of Ufa, 
<collectingCountry id="2BD57636FFFBFFE5E2F90649FB03F9EE" box="[963,1184,1554,1581]" name="Russia" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">Russian Federation</collectingCountry>
] a name subsequently replaced by 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFFBFFE5E01C066DFD70F992" authority="Krulikovsky, 1902" authorityName="Krulikovsky" authorityYear="1902" box="[294,723,1591,1617]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="phoebe" subSpecies="ufensis">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFFBFFE5E01C066DFE55F992" box="[294,502,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">M. phoebe ufensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFFBFFE5E33A066DFD70F992" author="Krulikovsky, A." box="[512,723,1591,1617]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" pagination="535 - 560" refId="ref9988" refString="Krulikovsky, A. (1902) On the fauna of Lepidoptera of the Yaroslavl Province. Horae Societatis Entomologicae Rossicae, 35, 535 - 560. [In Russian]" type="journal article" year="1902">Krulikovsky, 1902</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFFBFFE5E3DC066DFCEEF992" box="[742,845,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">uralensis</emphasis>
preoccupied by 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFFBFFE5E535066DFF70F9B6" authority="Eversmann, 1844" authorityName="Eversmann" authorityYear="1844" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="arduinna" subSpecies="uralensis">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFFBFFE5E535066DFAADF992" box="[1039,1294,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">M. arduinna uralensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFFBFFE5E42D066DFF70F9B6" author="Eversmann, E. F." pageId="3" pageNumber="28" refId="ref9016" refString="Eversmann, E. F. (1844) Fauna lepidopterologica Volgo-Uralensis. Exhibens. Lepidopterorum species quar per quinque annos in provinciis Volgam fluvium inter et montes Uralenses sitis observavit et descripsit. Typis Universitatis, Casani, 633 рp." type="book" year="1844">Eversmann, 1844</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFFBFFE5E1DC0601FE6AF9B6" author="Higgins, L. G." box="[230,457,1627,1653]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" pagination="175 - 365" refId="ref9372" refString="Higgins, L. G. (1941) An illustrated catalogue of the Palearctic Melitaea (Lep. Rhopalocera). Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London, 91, 175 - 365. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1941. tb 01045. x" type="journal article" year="1941">Higgins (1941: 343)</bibRefCitation>
equated this name to 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFFBFFE5E3870601FC2BF9B6" authority="Staudinger" authorityName="Staudinger" box="[701,904,1627,1653]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornata">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFFBFFE5E3870601FCABF9B7" box="[701,776,1627,1652]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">ornata</emphasis>
Staudinger
</taxonomicName>
(an error of authority). This synonymy with 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFFBFFE5E4440601FF41F95B" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornata">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFFBFFE5E4440601FF41F95B" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">M. ornata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was accepted by 
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFFBFFE5E09E0625FD46F95A" author="Russell, PJ &amp; Tennent, W. J." box="[420,741,1662,1689]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" pagination="27 - 56" refId="ref10922" refString="Russell, PJ. C. &amp; Tennent, W. J. (2016) A synonymic list of names associated with western Palaearctic Melitaea phoebe (Denis &amp; Schiffermuller, 1775) species group taxa M. phoebe; M. punica Oberthur, 1876; M. ornata Christoph, 1893) (Lepidoptera, Nymphalidae). Nota Lepidopterologica, 39 (1), 27 - 56. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / nl. 39.5929" type="journal article" year="2016">Russell &amp; Tennent (2016: 56</bibRefCitation>
, note 98); however, 
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFFBFFE5E2FD0625FAEEF959" author="Van Oorschot, H. &amp; Coutsis, J. G." box="[967,1357,1663,1690]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" refId="ref11693" refString="Van Oorschot, H. &amp; Coutsis, J. G. (2014) The genus Melitaea Fabricius, 1807 (Lepidoptera, Nymphalidae, Nymphalinae) Taxonomy and systematics with special reference to the male genitalia. Tshikolovets publications, Pardubice, Czech Republic, 360 pp." type="book" year="2014">van Oorschot &amp; Coutsis (2014: 60)</bibRefCitation>
placed it as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFFBFFE5E05B06F9FE75F97E" baseAuthorityName="Denis &amp; Schiffermuller" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[353,470,1699,1725]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoebe">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFFBFFE5E05B06F9FE75F97E" box="[353,470,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">M. phoebe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, possibly because they incorrectly synonymised 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFFBFFE5E2D706F9FBFFF97F" box="[1005,1116,1699,1724]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornata">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFFBFFE5E2D706F9FBFFF97F" box="[1005,1116,1699,1724]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">M. ornata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFFBFFE5E5AD06F9FAA8F97E" baseAuthorityName="Denis &amp; Schiffermuller" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[1175,1291,1699,1725]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoebe">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFFBFFE5E5AD06F9FAA8F97E" box="[1175,1291,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">M. phoebe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFFBFFE5E42206F9FEBCF922" author="Hesselbarth, G. &amp; van Oorschot, H. &amp; Wagener, S." pageId="3" pageNumber="28" pagination="1 - 847" refId="ref9287" refString="Hesselbarth, G., van Oorschot, H. &amp; Wagener, S. (1995) Die Tagfalter der Turkei unter Berucksichtigung der angrenzenden Lander, Sigbert Wagener, Bocholt, Germany, 1, 1 - 757, 2, 758 - 1354, 3, 1 - 847." type="journal article" year="1995">
Hesselbarth 
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFFBFFE5E1AD069DFF6CF922" box="[151,207,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">et al.</emphasis>
(1995)
</bibRefCitation>
overlooked this name. It is known that both 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFFBFFE5E237069DFC20F922" baseAuthorityName="Denis &amp; Schiffermuller" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[781,899,1735,1761]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoebe">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFFBFFE5E237069DFC20F922" box="[781,899,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">M. phoebe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFFBFFE5E282069DFB84F923" box="[952,1063,1735,1760]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornata">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFFBFFE5E282069DFB84F923" box="[952,1063,1735,1760]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">M. ornata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
fly in the southern Urals (
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFFBFFE5E472069DFEC2F8C6" author="Russell, P. J. C. &amp; Tennent, W. J." pageId="3" pageNumber="28" pagination="199 - 212" refId="ref11007" refString="Russell, P. J. C. &amp; Tennent, W. J. (2022) Butterflies observed on the western (European) slopes of the southern Ural Mountains during three spring visits in 2011, 2012 and 2014 (Lepidoptera Papilionoidea). Neue Entomologische Nachrichten 80: 199 - 212. [including 8 colour plates]" type="journal article" year="2022">Russell &amp; Tennent (2022)</bibRefCitation>
, see 
<figureCitation id="CBF92A23FFFBFFE5E0AC06B1FDADF8C6" box="[406,526,1771,1797]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1717,1741]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,200,1692]" captionTargetId="figure-26@2.[151,1436,181,1693]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. 1, Melitaea ornata male underside, Russian Federation, southern Urals, Orenburg Province, Guberli, ca. 190 m, 14 May 2014. 2, Melitaea phoebe male underside, Russian Federation, southern Urals, Orenburg Province, Krasnoznamenka, ca. 210 m, 16 May 2014. 3, Melitaea ornata female underside, Slovenia, Koper, ca. 2km NW of Rakitovec ca. 525 m, 17 May 2011. 4, Melitaea phoebe female underside, Slovenia, Koper, ca. 2km S. of Rakitovec ca. 525 m, 17 May 2011. 5, Lectotype female of Melitaea phoebe caucasica Staudinger, 1870. 6, Paralectotype male of Melitaea phoebe caucasica Staudinger, 1870. Figs 1–4 © P. Russell. Figs 5–6 © T. Léger. A = upperside, B = underside, C = labels on specimen pin." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577631" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577631/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">Figs 1 &amp; 2</figureCitation>
). Anikin 
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFFBFFE5E34F06B1FD0EF8C6" box="[629,685,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">et al.</emphasis>
(2017: 522) and 
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFFBFFE5E25606B1FB75F8C6" author="Kostjuk I. Y. &amp; Zolotuhin V. V." box="[876,1238,1771,1797]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" pagination="586 - 593" refId="ref9806" refString="Kostjuk I. Y. &amp; Zolotuhin V. V. (2017) The types of moths and butterflies described from the Volga-Ural Region by Leonid Krulikowsky (Krulikovsky). Part 2. Macrolepidoptera. In: Anikin V. V., Sachkov S. A., Zolotuhin, V. V. (Eds.), Fauna lepidopterologica Volgo-Uralensis: from P. Pallas to present days. Munich-Vilnius. Proceedings of the Museum Witt. Munich, 7, 443 - 450, 586 - 593." type="journal article" year="2017">Kostjuk &amp; Zolotuhin (2017: 446</bibRefCitation>
&amp; plate 24, fig 4) figured the ‘Typus’, a specimen taken at Ufa on 
<date id="277C1066FFFBFFE5E3940755FCE1F8EA" box="[686,834,1807,1833]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" value="1894-06-10">10 June 1894</date>
(= 24 June in today’s Gregorian calendar, not adopted in 
<collectingCountry id="2BD57636FFFBFFE5E1890769FF5DF88E" box="[179,254,1843,1869]" name="Russia" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">Russia</collectingCountry>
until 
<date id="277C1066FFFBFFE5E0040769FE47F88E" box="[318,484,1843,1869]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" value="1918-02">February 1918</date>
), which they designated as the 
<typeStatus id="8C798804FFFBFFE5E2040769FC0BF88E" box="[830,936,1843,1869]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">lectotype</typeStatus>
. The specimen is figured here with the labels (
<figureCitation id="CBF92A23FFFBFFE5E1A5070DFEFCF8B2" box="[159,351,1879,1905]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1857,1881]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,560,1833]" captionTargetId="figure-219@4.[151,1436,560,1833]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–11. 7, Lectotype of Melitaea phoebe sibina Alphéraky, 1881. 8, Melitaea phoebe ab. tatara Krulikovsky, 1891. 9, Lectotype of Melitaea phoebe ornata Christoph, 1893. 10, Lectotype of Melitaea phoebe uralensis Krulikovsky, 1897 (= ufensis Krulikovsky 1902). 11, Lectotype of Melitaea phoebe var. tungusa Herz, 1899. Figs 7, 9, 11 © V.A. Lukhtanov. Figs 8, 10 © expired. A = upperside, B = underside, C = labels on specimen pin." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577635" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577635/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">Figures 10A &amp; B</figureCitation>
). From the underside of the specimen it can be seen that the submarginal black arches are slim and touch the intervening veins and the antenna are club-shaped rather than spatulate; thus the present authors consider that this specimen is 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFFBFFE5E0B907C5FE59F87A" baseAuthorityName="Denis &amp; Schiffermuller" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[387,506,1951,1977]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoebe">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFFBFFE5E0B907C5FE59F87A" box="[387,506,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">M. phoebe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
rather than 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFFBFFE5E3B807C5FD51F87B" box="[642,754,1951,1976]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornata">
